        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          Home EV charger installation also opens the door to smart features that enhance your charging experience. Most modern chargers come equipped with Wi-Fi connectivity, enabling you to control and monitor charging sessions through smartphone apps. These smart features let you track energy usage, set charging schedules, and even integrate with your smart home system for maximum efficiency. If you have solar panels, some chargers can use solar energy to power your electric vehicle, further reducing your reliance on the grid and lowering your carbon footprint.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          To install an EV charger at home, you'll typically need off street parking and a suitable electricity meter. The installation process usually starts with a home survey to assess your property's electrical setup and determine the best charger location. Most UK homes are suitable for a standard installation, which can be completed in just a few hours. For properties with more complex requirements, such as longer cable runs or unique charger locations, an enhanced installation may be necessary, which could involve additional costs.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
